snippet.textDisplay:
Pokemon armor...Another trio of Regi making them 6 in total if there's a design not shown. Elec' looks like body/wing, Draco' looks like a head, obviously. That would make the 3 originals and new one arms/legs. Regigigas have 6 spheres on his body too...Interesting

Phase 1:
Armored Regigigas (The 6 regi in armor form try to seal Gigas losing control?)
Phase 2:
"Slow start" ends, the armor breaks and Regigigas body is ready. (aura/gigantamax?)
Rematches:
The armor fragments turn into pokemon forms again,
Regigigas is so exausted he have his normal stats again.

You can only have 6 pokemons, so by these rules you'll never be able to use armored Regigigas...Unless one of them turn into an item or there's only 5 Regis...Oh boy. That would be a daring risk/reward strategy to basically use only "one" special pokemon per matches as postgame bonus for the solo adventure, even if he's basically in god-mode. ._.

Or...
Super mega badass Megazord Ragigigas knight using the sword and shield! I know the fandom will make the fanart happens...The idea is so ridiculous t's their duty at this point. xD

They have a golden opportunity to make a super fun and challenging boss battle right there, let's wait and see what they have in store for this DLC.

snippet.textDisplay: So you have to buy both games to experience both "expansion passes" instead of buying one game with an almost different story mode and bonus material (battle frontier). It's a shame to see where Pokemon is going in regards to it's "story mode." This whole adding DLCs and having to buy both games. Yes, Pokemon have always been version exclusive, but this whole DLC thing for new locations is a little disappointing. For what it's worth, this will be the first year where I do not buy the game.
